cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the impact of fronthaul latency on the performance of ARQ protocols in C-RAN systems, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of signal-to-interference ratio on different ARQ protocols, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance of communication protocols in C-RAN systems, which falls under the communications and networking category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper models the C-RAN system as a multi-dimensional Markov process, which is a systems and control problem. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the benefits and drawbacks of centralized processing in C-RAN systems, which is related to distributed and parallel computing.
